  <description><![CDATA[<!-- <p><img height="112" width="841" align="middle" rel="841,112" src="/media/6416544/fairmont-banff-springs-banner.jpg" /></p> -->
<p>A world famous hotel, the old Baronial splendour of the Fairmont Banff Springs never fails to amaze. </p>
<h2>Castle in the Rockies</h2>
<p>Virtually a resort in itself the hotel is nestled at the foot of the Rockies in extensive grounds with superb views of the wilderness. The ski bus will pick you up from the hotel for transport to all three ski areas.</p>
<h2>Dining</h2>
<p>The hotel houses a variety of restaurant and dining options. You can try prime cuts of Alberta beef at the 1888 Chop House, or dig into classic French &amp; Canadian dishes at the Vermillion Room.</p>
<h2>Fairmont Spa</h2>
<p>The final word in relaxation, the Fairmont's Spa is a sanctuary for pampering and rejuvenation in the mountains. The 3,700m<sup>2</sup> wellness area includes indoor and outdoor salt water pools, hot tub, three waterfall treatment whirlpools, wading pool, mineral pool, outdoor whirlpool, eucalyptus room, sauna and relaxation rooms.</p>]]></description>
